### Claims API Tests
# Run these tests in sequence after creating an item. Make sure to replace tokens and IDs.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:10000/api
@ownerToken = your_owner_jwt_token_here
@claimantToken = your_claimant_jwt_token_here
@itemId = item_id_here
@claimId = claim_id_here

###
# 1. Submit a claim (Run as claimant)
POST {{baseUrl}}/claims
Authorization: Bearer {{claimantToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "itemId": "{{itemId}}",
  "reason": "This is my missing ID card. The picture matches me and it has my student ID number on it."
}

###
# 2. Get my claims (Run as claimant)
GET {{baseUrl}}/claims/my-claims
Authorization: Bearer {{claimantToken}}

###
# 3. Get received claims (Run as owner)
GET {{baseUrl}}/claims/received
Authorization: Bearer {{ownerToken}}

###
# 4. Accept a claim (Run as owner)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/claims/{{claimId}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{ownerToken}}

###
# 5. Reject a claim (Run as owner)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/claims/{{claimId}}/reject
Authorization: Bearer {{ownerToken}}
